    <title>Butter Chicken</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Butter Chicken</h1>
    <img src="https://images.openai.com/static-rsc-4/vp5O1DFazFuwn_WqZBxHHfRRfK3JxbZ4j-dRI00EgkKw-lef4E8qwKTueg71XM5F9d1kIMVK_RAMbdKnQ8B1L4EjLtCPpB3ox738jxC7flcpqSmmpVmeL88dVjnj7-KhLb7g-ssE19QLZ8M_3kFCCMjnv9AjqqR2AGpIj57Up6DqY5kLgx1WiYZx-wXFQFc3?purpose=fullsize" alt="Butter Chicken" width="540">
    <p>A delicious and creamy Indian dish made with tender chicken pieces cooked in a rich tomato-based sauce with butter and cream.</p>
    <h2>Ingredients:</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>500g chicken</li>
        <li>1 tbsp ginger-garlic paste</li>
        <li>1 tsp turmeric</li>
        <li>1 tsp chili powder</li>
        <li>Salt</li>
        <li>2 tomatoes</li>
        <li>1 onion</li>
        <li>2 tbsp butter</li>
        <li>1 tbsp cream</li>
        <li>1 tsp garam masala</li>
        <li>1 tsp kasuri methi</li>
        <li>1 cup curd/yogurt</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>Steps:</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>Marinate chicken with curd, turmeric, chili powder, salt, and ginger-garlic paste for 1 hour.</li>
        <li>Cook or grill the chicken pieces.</li>
        <li>Heat butter in a pan and sauté onions until golden.</li>
        <li>Add garam masala and kasuri methi.</li>
        <li>Add cooked chicken and simmer for 10 minutes.</li>
        <li>Add cream and mix well.</li>
        <li>Serve hot with naan or rice</li>
        <li>Add tomato puree and cook until oil separates.</li>
    </ol>
